body:
Install with nuget on visual studio :
# PM> Install-Package IxMail 

after installation, you web config will change and add this 
`
 <system.net>
    <mailSettings>
      <!-- Method#1: Configure smtp server credentials -->
      <smtp from="user@gmail.com">
        <network enableSsl="true" host="smtp.gmail.com" port="587" userName="user@gmail.com" password="password" />
      </smtp>

      <!-- Method#2: Dump emails to a local directory -->
      <!--
			<smtp from="some-email@gmail.com" deliveryMethod="SpecifiedPickupDirectory">
				<network host="localhost"/>
				<specifiedPickupDirectory pickupDirectoryLocation="c:\temp\"/>
			</smtp>
			-->
    </mailSettings>
  </system.net>
`

send mail
`
  using (IxMailMessage iM = new IxMailMessage())
            {
                // an object to send
                iM.mailBody = new SelectListItem { Value = "Value", Text = "Text", Selected = true };

                // email to
                iM.To.Add("ix.habibi@gmail.com");

                iM.Subject = "IxMail async";

                //your tamplate
                iM.tamplateMail = "mytamplate.html";

                // your subject
                // async send mail, wich background proses, improve speed load your web
                EmailSender.SendMailAsync(iM);
            }
`
Add your custom tamplates inside hidden folder **IxMail**, after you try, send a mail for testing :D
if got something error, you can also see hidden folder in **IxMail**
